{
  "texts": [
    "This is also reflected in the increase of the UA odds over time (UA over RU consistently, UA over EN as war continues).",
    "Figure 4c reports behavioural language changes across all three language pairs, when controlling for the user turnover.",
    "For RU over EN we see a constant decline in the odds over time (-38% to tweet in RU), which further speeds up once aggression starts (-51%).",
    "For UA over EN we see the exact opposite, as over time users are more likely to tweet in UA (+64% in odds).",
    "This change reverses with the start of aggression and the outbreak of the war (-34%), but subsequently reaches pre-aggression levels as the war unfolds."
  ]
}